│ behavior, it constructs vectors for gathers/scatters via helper methods. The  │
│ issue is consistent with incorrect choice of insertion point when creating    │
│ these vector instructions.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nSLPVectorizer places   │
│ newly created vector instructions at an insertion point based on one of the   │
│ scalar instructions in the tree (often the \"getInsertionPoint\" of the       │
│ scheduling region or a representative instruction). In CFGs with many         │
│ branches and phis, some users of the newly built vector may reside in         │
│ different blocks that are not dominated by the chosen insertion point.        │
│ Creating a broadcast vector of a pointer (%arg) in a specific block and then  │
│ using it in non-dominated blocks triggers the verifier error.\nTherefore, the │
